  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You gain the ability to magically steal the knowledge of how to cast a spell from another spellcaster.</p><p>Immediately after a creature casts a spell that targets you or includes you in its area of effect, you can take a Reaction to force the creature to make an Intelligence saving throw. The DC equals your spell save DC. On a failed save, you negate the spell's effect against you, and you steal the knowledge of the spell if it is at least level 1 and of a level you can cast (it doesn't need to be a Wizard spell). For the next 8 hours or until you use this feature again, you have the spell prepared. The creature can't cast that spell until the 8 hours have passed or you have used this feature again.</p><p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Proficiency Bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.</p>",
